From: "Barak A. Pearlmutter" <barak+git@pearlmutter.net>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 15:59:13 +0100
Subject: out-of-tree include derived

The source tarball contains src/makefile.h (with bad syntax) and
src/builttag.hh. With an out-of-tree build, these can be included
instead of the built one. Changing each of the #include "makefile.h"
lines into #include <makefile.h> solves the issue, because it just
uses the -I's in order instead of first doing a source-file-relative
search.

Same for #include "builttag.hh", although it does not actually break
the build.

Long term, these files should not be included in the tarball anyway.
---
 src/Archive.cc         | 2 +-
 src/NativeFunction.cc  | 2 +-
 src/UserPreferences.cc | 4 ++--
 src/main.cc            | 4 ++--
 4 files changed, 6 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/Archive.cc b/src/Archive.cc
index 7368b0d..30f6e0e 100644
--- a/src/Archive.cc
+++ b/src/Archive.cc
@@ -27,7 +27,7 @@
 #include <sys/types.h>
 
 #include "Archive.hh"
-#include "buildtag.hh"   // for ARCHIVE_SVN
+#include <buildtag.hh>   // for ARCHIVE_SVN
 #include "Common.hh"
 #include "Command.hh"
 #include "CharCell.hh"
diff --git a/src/NativeFunction.cc b/src/NativeFunction.cc
index a148442..68fab89 100644
--- a/src/NativeFunction.cc
+++ b/src/NativeFunction.cc
@@ -25,7 +25,7 @@
 #include <unistd.h>
 
 #include "Error.hh"
-#include "makefile.h"
+#include <makefile.h>
 #include "NativeFunction.hh"
 #include "Symbol.hh"
 #include "Workspace.hh"
diff --git a/src/UserPreferences.cc b/src/UserPreferences.cc
index b1bbb40..c3eba81 100644
--- a/src/UserPreferences.cc
+++ b/src/UserPreferences.cc
@@ -27,7 +27,7 @@
 
 #include "config.h"
 
-#include "buildtag.hh"
+#include <buildtag.hh>
